Style:
- Black background for the section
- Tags: `border border-white/20 text-white/80 font-mono text-sm px-4 py-2`
- PRIMARY tags get `border-brutal-yellow text-brutal-yellow` to stand out
- INFRASTRUCTURE tags stay `border-white/30 text-white/60`
- INTEGRATIONS tags get `border-white/20 text-white/40` — dimmest
- Category labels ("PRIMARY:", "INFRASTRUCTURE:", "INTEGRATIONS:") in `text-white/30 font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase`
- The quote stays at the bottom, `text-white/50 font-mono text-sm italic`

This is more CTO-like — organized, categorized, intentional. A scrolling ticker says "I know stuff." A categorized grid says "I've made deliberate technology choices."

